# Force LF line endings for files that are read by Linux containers or POSIX
# shells. Without this, Windows checkouts with core.autocrlf=true write CRLF
# to disk; Docker reads the working-tree file. The credential helper line
# in the Dockerfile, in particular, will store literal \r characters inside
# its git config value, and `git fetch` against private GitHub repos fails
# with an opaque "Authentication failed" — silently broken from a CRLF.

Dockerfile         text eol=lf
.dockerignore      text eol=lf
*.sh               text eol=lf
*.yml              text eol=lf
*.yaml             text eol=lf
